        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Oh mages are supposed to be *THE* pet class alright.  VI mentioned a long time ago that mages were supposed to be the #1 pet-class, and necros the #2 pet-class (this was pre-Beastlord I'm not sure how they envisioned BLs).  Thus far, this has held true.  Mages have better pets than necros in EVERY sphere up to and including the EoT.  Have our rogue pet go at their water pet sometimes - it's no real contest, nor is our 56 monk pet versus any of their Greater Vocerations.  </P><P>The ONLY reason EoT won that duel is because it lifetaps while the mage water casts some 100+ damage DD that isn't hitting because its target is a level 60 necro with ample resistances.  It is not a fair duel for more than one reason, but it's TRULY not fair because its not a match against a mob but a DUEL.  It reflects to NO DEGREE the true ability of a mage pet against real mobs.  Not only are mages whining about a problem that doesn't exist, but they're downplaying their own abilities in order to make themselves look better.  </P><P>Now if the mages were complaining that their pets' DDs aren't landing on uber mobs because of level differences and resistances - I'd support them, but when they're asking for FULL-FLEDGED buffs to their own pets in order to make them vastly superior to the EoT in a duel that involves no DS, they're going too far, stepping on too many toes, and vastly undermining balance for their own benefits.  If I had ANY respect for the Magician's Tower it's gone now.  The few posters there who actually possess some common sense are drowned out by the majority of mage-whiners who still seem to be suffering some kind of selective memory blur where they just kindly forgot all about what happened the last time mages whined about necro pets.</P><P><BR>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
