         <BR>This post is simply my opinion, not trying to start a war...</P><P>I honestly do not support any nerf to EoT not that it matters to you folks.  Call me a whiny bitch all you want but me and my fellow mages have suffered the nerf bat just as much and just as bad as you have.</P><P>I will be blunt, all mages have going for them are their pets and their 3rd rate nukes.  We have no snare, fear, or ports to safe area of a zone, In my opinion we should not have these defensive abilities.</P><P>In exchange for not having them we should however have the best pets. </P><P>We get pressed into slavery as mod rod 2 factories on raids and the ocasional CoH.  Our pets are not used much on raids, nor our our nukes.  We use our pets and our nukes to solo and exp group.  We do not have the defensive capabilties that you have, we do not have fear or snare.  Because of this our pets need to tank and need to be able to tank.  If they are not then we soon need to run to the zone, gate, or die.</P><P>We all want to be "the best",  I think however each non-hybrid class should be "the best" in one area and maybe second or third or whatever "best" in others.</P><P>I think the following should hold true:</P><P><BR>Best Healer = Cleric<BR>Best Puller = Monk<BR>Best Tank = Warrior<BR>Best Melee Damage = Rogue<BR>Best Crowd Control = Enchanter<BR>Best Slow/Debuff = Shaman<BR>Best Caster Damage = Wizard<BR>Best Dots & Overall Soloability = Necromancer<BR>Jack of all Trades master of NONE = Druid<BR>Best at Group Support = Bard<BR>Best Pets = Magician</P><P>It does not however, too many classes step on each other.  It can be argued that in many zones a DC Enchanter, Necromancer, or Druid can have the "best" pets.  it can also be argued that Monks and Rangers can outdamage Rouges under many conditons.  It has even been argued that Pally's (not even a primary class) can our heal clerics and priest classes in some situations.</P><P>VI/SoE has screwed up any notion of class balance to the point that only a handful of classes will be happy at all.</P><P>I never asked for Mod Rod 2, I never wanted to step on the role of the Enchanter class in its monopoly on mana regen.  I was perfectly happy when Magicians were loved in exp groups and when we had the 2nd best nukes.  That changed and it changed a while ago,  I suppose many of us that held on should have leveled up something new.</P><P>I won't be happy until mages firmly have the best pets and until those pets are able to allow us the freedom to solo that is enjoyed by Druids and wizards.  I did not make a mage to be a mod rod 2 jockey for some class bigot jerk (most raid leaders I have met excluding myself).</P><P>I don't want EoT nerfed!<BR>I don't want EoT nerfed!</P><P>I say make all pets better but at least give mages soimehting damage oriented to be "best" in.</P><P>Flame away kids... have fun.. and peace.</P><P></P><P><BR>Master Rthen Majere<BR>Arch Mage<BR>Master of the Orb</P><P>Edited by - Rthen on 08/12/2002  13:31:14<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
