        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=58324&amp;TOPIC_ID=7029&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Looks+like+we+have+another+pissing+contest&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         </P><P>Sadly your opinion is one that VI/SoE seems to share.  I can only hope somone over there at VI/SoE plays a mage to level 60+ and sees just how bad it really is.</P><P>I can in brief tell you why the many deffensive abilities of the necro combined with a comparable pet (to the mage) adds up to an unbalance, since necros can:</P><P>1.  Fear <BR>2.  Snare<BR>3.  DoT (they have the best DoT's)<BR>4.  Nuke (yes they do have nukes)</P><P>They hardly even need a pet to begin with, I have seen many solo wihout one, nice trick.. mages can't so that :-).  Now lets add:</P><P>1.  Necro Normal Pet<BR>2.  EoT (level 59)<BR>3.  Dire Charmed pet  (59 + 24 AA)</P><P>Add one of these and you can solo mobs fast and like a factory.  While a mage would go OOM and have to go hide and med someplace.</P><P>In power you are really 3 classes,  your a pet class like a mage,  a damage caster class with the best dots and some lower end nukes, and your a gimped cleric since you can heal your pet (or any one for that matter) and for 500 pp a pop (EE) you can rez.</P><P>I'm sorry if a bunch of mages do not approve of or even remotely like the fact that after many stealth and upfront nerfs all they have is a pet thats now just slightly above yours and some nukes that are firmly 3rd place behind a priest class (Druid) that can solo 1 to 60 in a few months.  Only after completing an Epic quest that is one of the most insanely time consuming can a mage say they are indeed the "best" summoned pet caster.</P><P>Even then your Dire Charmed pets make my epic look silly.  </P><P>From my point of view necros have a lot going for them, thats great.  I am happy for you.</P><P>However mages need a damage dealing role and that direction should be with their pets.  It should not just be with epic pet but also with greater voc pets.  Across the board there should be some mage only upgrades to their pets.</P><P>Besides pet melee and spell raw damage which we still need more of, maybe some quest spells that summone bane damage weapons against dragon, giant, and other types of mobs as well.  Make these weapons pet only.</P><P>So we can give other pet casters these weps as well (in addiiton to muzzel).</P><P>I don't want to solo better then you and wihtout fear and snare I never will be able to.  I just want to be able to do damage and solo at least as well as a damn Wizard.  I think I deserve that much since I don't offer anything else to a raid besides mod rod 2 bitch.</P><P>Anyways again just my opinion.  I don't want EoT nerfed but I sure do want some nice upgrades for my class. </P><P></P><P><BR>Master Rthen Majere<BR>Arch Mage<BR>Master of the Orb<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
