        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         The focus item rarity seems to be an issue. </P><P>Why do you have 4 focus items?  Well, you don't.  You have 8 I believe.  Four for 1-50 and four different ones for 51-60.  </P><P>Necros just have the one.  They have to wait 46 levels to get it.  Used to be that it only dropped off Inny himself.  Rare drop then off of him too.  Necros also hardly ever go to Hate.  I've seen more necro focus books rot then I've seen looted.</P><P>Why do you need 4 for your high levels?  Well, you have options that we really don't.  We have one flavor of pet.  Granted, we do get the joy of getting a rogue and monk pet, but the rogue is nothing special and the monk is only useful if you're very careful.</P><P>Look, dueling pets is a bad way to gauge mage pets against necro pets.  The new resist rules and different tactics used makes it difficult to gauge.</P><P>How are some ways that mage pets are hands down better then any necro pet?</P><P>Cast time<BR>Mana Cost<BR>Ease of getting reagents (bone chips vs. gems)<BR>And in the case of EoT, the cost of summoning the pet in pp</P><P>Your pets should have more melee ability then a necro, but I don't think it should be a vast ammount.  Your pets should (and do I think) have more HP's then our pets.</P><P>Many mages argue that their epic pet shouldn't be counted against them when this arguement takes place.  So, what, you think that your regular pets should be closer to your epic pet?  Well then why the hell would anyone want to bother with your epic quest!!!</P><P>Your quest is an absolute bugger.  It is a major bitch.  It is hard as hell.  However, it is also awsome.  No other epic changes the class in a positive as much as yours.  Clerics have a love hate relationship with theirs cause they feel like a click slave.  You, however, don't have to deal with that.  </P><P>No epic is more important in the high level game then the Cleric epic.</P><P>No epic is more important to a class then the mage epic, in my opinion.</P><P>I'll trade a mage any day.  He can have the EoT and my peri's AND my epic snare staff, if he gives me a chance to have his epic quest and its rewards instead.</P><P>Pre-Paineel Eruidte Necro<BR>Brell Serilis<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
